RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 1 400 Y Dirt CR: 71. Allowance Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MS CLARA responded to threats in the stretch and held firm. DECIDER CARTEL QUEEN jostled away, rallied outside under right-handed encouragement, and won the nod for place honors. APPRECIATE bumped leaving, closed gamely late, and was out nodded for second. TULSA TIMBER broke awkwardly, and flew late. TIMBERS MOON lacked kick needed. FIRECRUNCH lacked a bid. TIMBER BUNNY crowded leaving, and was unable to recover the ground lost from the start.

ENTRY.NAME: Decider Cartel Queen

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 75. Maiden Special Weight Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIFES ADVENTURE set a pressured pace from the two path, was given his cue into the lane, and opened up under a strong hand ride, winning handily. DADDY'S PEPPER stalked inside under a snug hold, rallied into the stretch, edged away, and held safely for place. AL REICHERT prompted the pace from the four path, rallied between foes at the head of the stretch and inched clear to secure show. SIX SHOTS OF T tracked outside from the five path, battled four wide into the stretch, and weakened. TAPFERSURE unhurried early, sat in striking distance, and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD THREE YEAR OLDS, 120 LBS.; OLDER, 125 LBS. Claiming Price $16,000 AB Bred Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BUNNY NOREEN contested the early pace inside of GHOSTLY RUNNER, drew clear in the far turn, opened up willingly through the stretch, and was geared down to score easily. TENDER LOVE chased wide through the backstretch, closed gradually, and won the nod for place. WICKED WIZZY rated well off the pace while five wide, cut the corner into the far turn, chased the leader through the stretch but was no match, and was caught in the final strides. SMOKIN JOY carried wide early, and passed tiring rivals. HERE'S LEXIE chased the early pacesetters, and came up empty in the drive. GHOSTLY RUNNER vied three wide for the early lead, sat just off the leader, and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Bunny Noreen
ENTRY.COMMENT: contested pace, drew clear, opened up, geared down

ENTRY.NAME: Tender Love
ENTRY.OWNER: Brigden William R Guest Trent and Erikson Dan

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 77. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 OR LESS IN THEIR LAST THREE STARTS AND HAVE NOT WON A STARTER SINCE STARTING FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000(AB $10,000) OR LESS OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $12,5 00. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ADDYDIDIT showed good early speed to fan four wide in the opening turn, sat just off of the pacesetter, lodged a bid nearing the eighth pole, and dug in to win the bob. GO MAMA was unhurried early then assumed the lead entering the backstretch, saved ground while showing the way, responded to ADDYDIDIT in the drive, and was narrowly denied. SKY DESTINY took back leaving the opening turn, hustled three wide in the final turn, and closed gradually. WHISKARITA raced five to six wide through the first turn, chased outside in the far turn, and improved late. IT'S ALEXUS was outsprinted in the opening turn, saved ground inside, and went evenly through the stretch. EXACTLY stalked four wide, and had nothing left in the late stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Whiskarita
ENTRY.OWNER: Dialed In Racing Stable and Johannsen Kevin

ENTRY.NAME: Addydidit
ENTRY.COMMENT: early speed 4w, stalked outside, dug in, won bob

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 51. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $6,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VALENTINO ROSSA rated well off the pace while wide through the backstretch, moved up closer into striking distance, urged along into the lane, and won driving. PUNCH PERFECT trailed the field, angled inside to the rail at the head of the stretch, and finished well getting by for place. LANA'S PRETTY GIRL set a pressured pace from between foes, dueled inside of TAPULOUS in the final turn, was overtaken and gave way grudgingly after a long drive. TAPULOUS pressed while four to five wide, fanned three wide leaving the backstretch, dueled outside of LANA'S PRETTY GIRL in the final turn, and weakened late stretch. BAKED N WIRED fractious in gate, sat just off the pace from a rail position, and was through early.

ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, dueled inside, gave way

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 83. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 19500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR RESTRICTED STAKES RACE IN ALBERTA OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $17,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $17,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $22,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MUDINATOR contested the early pace from the four path, was unable to move on with READYTOTAPNSING in the far turn, was kept on under steady handling through the stretch, dug in to take over in the final yards. READYTOTAPNSING dueled for the lead under a strong hold leaving the chute, edged away in the final turn, was under steady pressure through the stretch and was overcome in the later yards. FOUR O SIX CREED raced seven wide entering the backstretch, circled the field into the lane, closed well outside and missed. NORTHERN JEWEL raced at the back of the pack, and rallied belatedly. BIG BAD INTAGLIO sat just off the dueling pacesetters, brushed LAHUN at the head of the lane, angled inside then weakened. ARISTOCRACY sat along the rail under a snug hold early, and failed to threaten in the drive. LAHUN raced the widest into the backstretch, moved up into striking range while four to five wide, was knocked off stride when brushed near the three-sixteenth pole, and yielded. SHURAZ showed speed early while in traffic, and lost interest. LIL ZAPPER flashed early speed and tired.

Alberta Bred Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CARRIE'S SUCCESS saved ground from the three path, set sights on SMILIN EVIE into the lane then took over, and kicked clear. SMILIN EVIE vied from the three path for the lead, moved clear in the final turn was overtaken into the stretch and finished second best. TALA saved ground early, uncorked a late run for a good show finish. TAKE CHARGE GWEN jostled away, steadied in traffic entering the far turn, drove five wide under encouragement, and rallied belatedly. DAZZLING CHIC rallied belatedly. CHATTY GAL stalked the early pacesetters from the five path, and lacked a closing response. LITTLE ROSALYN lacked a clear path early, lodged a mild bid, and faded. KERIK lagged early and offered a late mild bid. WHEELSUPINTHIRTY bumped away from the gate, and lacked a bid. WITHIN REASON contended the early pace outside of SMILIN EVIE, was unable to move on with foe, and yielded at the top of the lane.
